- Homer, this is serious.

239
00:17:16,810 --> 00:17:18,380
Oh, it is not.

240
00:17:23,270 --> 00:17:26,950
Roman numeral three:
Surprise boy in bed--

241
00:17:27,430 --> 00:17:28,320
[ Slurps ]

242
00:17:28,980 --> 00:17:31,910
and, uh, disembowel him.

243
00:17:32,500 --> 00:17:35,470
No, I don't like that ''bowel'' in there.
Gut him.

244
00:17:36,160 --> 00:17:38,460
Ah, le motjuste.
[ Kisses ]

245
00:17:39,110 --> 00:17:40,500
[ Groaning ]

246
00:17:45,010 --> 00:17:48,360
- Bart, you want some brownie before 
you go to bed? - [ Screams ]

247
00:17:48,680 --> 00:17:51,020
Come on. Let me cut you a brownie
while they're still hot.

248
00:17:51,330 --> 00:17:53,670
[ Sighs ]
Dad, I'm kind of edgy right now.

249
00:17:54,080 --> 00:17:58,100
I'd appreciate you not coming in my room
screaming and brandishing a butcher knife.

250
00:17:58,400 --> 00:18:03,260
Why? Oh, right.
The Sideshow Bob thing.

251
00:18:03,560 --> 00:18:05,240
Oh, I'm sorry, boy.

252
00:18:08,620 --> 00:18:11,150
[ Loudly ] Bart, do you want to see
my new chainsaw and hockey mask?

253
00:18:11,480 --> 00:18:14,140
- [ Screams ]
- Oh, sorry.

254
00:18:14,460 --> 00:18:16,020
What am I thinking?

255
00:18:27,430 --> 00:18:28,600
[ Grumbles ]

256
00:18:35,620 --> 00:18:37,990
- [ Door Opens ]
- Hello, Bart.

257
00:18:38,290 --> 00:18:41,400
- Mom! Dad!
- Your family can't help you now.

258
00:18:41,840 --> 00:18:44,810
- [ All Grunting ]
- [ Homer Snoring ]

259
00:18:45,240 --> 00:18:48,670
- Oh, no, Dad's been drugged.
- No, he hasn't.

260
00:19:00,390 --> 00:19:02,390
- [ Chomps ]
- Uh-oh.

261
00:19:02,830 --> 00:19:03,830
[ Panting ]

262
00:19:05,300 --> 00:19:07,320
- [ Electrical Charges ]
- Oh!

263
00:19:08,530 --> 00:19:09,850
[ Panting ]

264
00:19:11,090 --> 00:19:12,760
- [ Chomps ]
- Oh, yeah.

265
00:19:13,520 --> 00:19:16,590
Well, Bart, any last requests?

266
00:19:17,030 --> 00:19:19,720
Well, there is one, but--

267
00:19:21,970 --> 00:19:23,630
- Nah.
- No, go on.

268
00:19:24,040 --> 00:19:26,910
Well, you have
such a beautiful voice.

269
00:19:27,200 --> 00:19:29,320
- Guilty as charged.
- Uh-huh.

270
00:19:29,710 --> 00:19:34,580
Anyway, I was wondering if you could sing
the entire score of the H.M.S. Pinafore.

271
00:19:34,920 --> 00:19:36,200
Very well, Bart.

272
00:19:36,470 --> 00:19:40,480
I shall send you to heaven
before I send you to hell.

273
00:19:41,680 --> 00:19:45,230
And a-two, and a-three, and--
"We sail the ocean blue "

274
00:19:45,230 --> 00:19:47,240
"And our saucy ship's
a beauty "

275
00:19:47,540 --> 00:19:51,930
"We are sober men and true
and attentive to our duty "

276
00:19:52,510 --> 00:19:55,420
" I'm called Little Buttercup "

277
00:19:55,770 --> 00:19:57,580
" Poor Little Buttercup "

278
00:19:57,960 --> 00:20:01,430
"Though I could never tell why "

279
00:20:02,100 --> 00:20:04,560
- [ Crunching ]
- "What, never? No, never "

280
00:20:04,930 --> 00:20:06,300
"What, never "

281
00:20:07,090 --> 00:20:11,440
" Hardly ever
He's hardly ever sick at sea "

282
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:17,020
"For he himself has said it "

283
00:20:17,550 --> 00:20:21,690
"And it's clearly to his credit "

284
00:20:22,400 --> 00:20:26,430
"That he is an Englishman "

285
00:20:26,980 --> 00:20:30,780
" He remains an E-E-E-En "

286
00:20:33,150 --> 00:20:35,030
" Glish "

287
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:37,370
" Man "

288
00:20:46,160 --> 00:20:47,830
[ Footsteps Approaching ]

289
00:20:48,730 --> 00:20:51,470
And now... the final curtain.

290
00:20:55,120 --> 00:20:57,750
- [ Grunts, Groans ]
- [ Gun Cocks ]

291
00:20:58,470 --> 00:21:01,700
Hold it right there, Sideshow Bob.
You're under arrest.

292
00:21:02,050 --> 00:21:04,290
By Lucifer's beard!

293
00:21:04,630 --> 00:21:07,970
Ah, yeah. It's a good thing
you drifted by this brothel.

294
00:21:09,350 --> 00:21:10,510
[ Police Radio Chatter ]

295
00:21:11,130 --> 00:21:12,690
I knew I had to
buy some time...

296
00:21:12,940 --> 00:21:15,850
so I asked him to sing the score
from the H.M.S. Pinafore.

297
00:21:16,130 --> 00:21:19,310
Ooh, a plan fiendishly
clever in its intricacies.

298
00:21:19,810 --> 00:21:21,520
Take him away, boys.

299
00:21:21,820 --> 00:21:24,640
Hey, I'm the chief here.
Bake him away, toys.

300
00:21:24,990 --> 00:21:27,260
- What'd you say, Chief?
- Do what the kid says.

301
00:21:30,810 --> 00:21:34,380
- Mm, it's so good to be home again.
- [ Tires Skid ]

302
00:21:34,770 --> 00:21:37,740
- Look what happened without my pills!
- [ Gasps ]

303
00:21:38,210 --> 00:21:40,570
Bart, run upstairs!
Get Grampa's medicine.

304
00:21:40,870 --> 00:21:44,890
Not so fast.
I wanna court this fair,young maiden.

305
00:21:46,090 --> 00:21:48,480
[ Grampa ]
There's somethin'you should know about me.

306
00:21:48,740 --> 00:21:50,640
[Jasper ]
I've got Steve and Eydie tickets.

307
00:21:50,910 --> 00:21:53,320
[ Grampa ]
I'm all yours.! [ Kisses ]

